        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-01-16 18:27:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nPeyton, were discussing this error with committers in chat, this one that you're picking up some errors, as powermock-api-mockito is not included.   I think this may have to do with move to jdk 11.   In any case, I guess we need you to use powermock-api-mockito2 dependency instead which is the one in policy/parent.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "9eba1c710bdf8586bfdfe69207af596718df547b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-01-16 20:29:40.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nensure that the m2 poms refer to powermock-api-mockito2 instead of powermock-api-mockito",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
